    "summary": "Walmart plans to remodel more than 650 U.S. stores and open about 20 new locations through 2026 and early 2027, advancing a modernization and expansion strategy. The effort focuses on Walmart store remodels with wider aisles, improved lighting, and enhanced pickup, delivery, and express options. New Walmart stores are planned or underway in California, Florida, Texas, and Arizona, with upgrades to pharmacies and vision centers. Select Neighborhood Market sites will add expanded deli and hot food, pharmacy delivery, and added space for online grocery fulfillment. Walmart said the initiative supports its low-price model, job creation, and eCommerce growth amid recent gains among higher‑income shoppers. It previously opened nine stores in 2025 and continues work to expand and upgrade more than 150 locations.",
